PLACEHOLDER -- not a real executable.

Tauri's build script requires this exact file to exist at this exact path
(binaries/backend-<target-triple>.exe) just to run `cargo check` / `cargo
build` / `pnpm tauri dev` successfully, even though the sidecar is only
ever spawned in a release build (see spawn_backend_sidecar in src/lib.rs).

Before running `pnpm tauri build` for real, REPLACE this file with the
actual PyInstaller-built backend executable:

  cd backend
  pip install -r requirements-dev.txt
  pyinstaller --onefile --name backend app/main.py
  copy dist\backend.exe ..\desktop\src-tauri\binaries\backend-x86_64-pc-windows-msvc.exe
